gnome-window-applets (0.2.9-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release:
    + WBA, WTA: Major code cleanups, rearangements and optimizations
    + WBA, WTA: Added plaintext settings backend (enable by setting
      PLAINTEXT_CONFIG to 1)
    + WBA, WTA: Fixed desktop detection (+ got rid of potential
      segfaults)
    + WBA: Bugfix: hide_on_unmaximized causes buttons to not reappear if
      disabled when currentwindow not present
    + WBA: Changed theme model from 16 to 24 images (added 2 new unfocused
      states) and made it backwards compatible
    + WBA: Fixed Compiz detection for maximized windows. Coincidentally
      this also makes Emerald work
    + WBA: Added new themes: Blubuntu, Equinox-Glass, Plano, New-Hope
    + WTA: Bugfix: Ensure the title gets truncated if it runs out of space
    + WTA: Forced the Expand option due to GTK+ bugs. It can be disabled in
      gconf-editor, but then you should also set a fixed title_size
    + WTA: Bugfix: Icon padding wrong on different panel orientations

 -- Filip Chabik <hadret@gmail.com>  Fri, 19 Nov 2010 19:22:21 +0100

